The Chicago Mercantile Exchange fined two stock-index-futures traders a total of $55,000 and suspended each trader for one month for allegedly making fraudulent trades last September. 

The Merc said it fined Frank Karkazis $30,000 and suspended his trading privileges for one month for allegedly disclosing a customer order in Standard & Poor's 500 stock-index futures last Sept. 28 to fellow trader Joseph Knapek before the order was offered to all traders in the pit. 

Mr. Knapek was fined $25,000 and suspended one month for allegedly having the order disclosed to him. 

Neither trader could be reached for comment. 

